bioghist.head: Historical or Biographical Note
bioghist.p: Founded in 1976, the Writer's Center is a non-profit community of writers supporting each other in the creation and marketing of literary texts. The Writer's Center annually conducts hundreds of workshops in various genres of writing. The Writer's Center also hosts literary events, readings and conferences; sells books and literary magazines

The Writer's Center is housed in a 12,200 square foot facility in the arts and entertainment district of Bethesda, Maryland, with workshops also offered in Leesburg and Arlington, Virginia, and at other locations around the greater Washington, D.C., metropolitan area.

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: This collection contains issues of the Carousel from 1978-2005, workshop brochures from between 1986-2002 and Poet Lore from 1978-2006.
